{"questionId":"19556","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Don took part in a project investigating wind speed,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo> </mo><msup><mtext>km h</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>, and the time, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi></math> minutes, to fully charge a solar powered robot.</p>\n<p>The investigation was carried out six times. The results are recorded in the table.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/7fae578ee2d78784d130772c4fd52752e5cc9780.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Calculate&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><menclose notation=\"top\"><mi>y</mi></menclose></math>, the mean time to fully charge the robot.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>32</mn></math>&nbsp; (minutes) &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><br>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"19556","referenceCode":"20N.2.SL.TZ0.T_1b.ii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Calculate y, the mean time to fully charge the robot.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.4—Pearsons, scatter diagrams, eqn of y on x"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}